Classes and Inheritance

Parent Class -> child class
variables/functions -> variables/functions +childVars/childFuncs


The child class can override the parent class.

When a child point to child one (static)


Object -> Actor -> Pawn -> Character

Object - store data - cannot be placed in a level.

  Components derived:
    1. UStaticMesh
    2. UTexture

Actor - can be placed in the level and can have a visual representation.

  Components derived:
    1. ACameraActor
    2. AHUD

Pawn - can be possessed by a controller.

  Components derived:
  1. AWheeledVehicle

Character - have a character movement component and have functionality appropriate for a character.
  Components derived:
  1. APaperCharacter.

